{"id":"220616603_The_Boyer-Moore-Galil_String_Searching_Strategies_Revisited","abstract":"Based on the Boyer-Moore-Galil approach, a new algorithm is proposed which requires a number of character comparisons bounded by 2n, regardless of the number of occurrences of the pattern in the textstring. Preprocessing is only slightly more involved and still requires a time linear in the pattern size.","authors":["Alberto Apostolico","Raffaele Giancarlo"],"meta":["February 1986SIAM Journal on Computing 15(1):98-105","DOI:10.1137/0215007","SourceDBLP"],"references":["220896787_On_Improving_the_Worst_Case_Running_Time_of_the_Boyer-Moore_String_Matching_Algorithm","220423622_Efficient_string_matching_An_aid_to_bibliographic_search","297131923_A_New_Proof_of_the_Linearity_of_the_Boyer-Moore_String_Searching_Algorithm","242500020_A_fast_string_searching_algorithm_commun","224960000_A_Fast_String_Searching_Algorithm","222617299_Time-space-optimal_string_matching","221499812_A_New_Proof_of_the_Linearity_of_the_Boyer-Moore_String_Searching_Algorithm","220618247_Fast_Pattern_Matching_in_Strings","220618222_The_Complexity_of_Pattern_Matching_for_a_Random_String","220617898_A_Correct_Preprocessing_Algorithm_for_Boyer-Moore_String-Searching"]}